  <prompt>
    Create the AttachmentArtifact (sprk_attachmentartifact) table in Dataverse to track
    email attachments that are saved as separate documents. Link to the parent EmailArtifact
    and the resulting Document entity.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Dataverse developer and data modeler. Expert in Power Platform schema design and
    relationship configuration.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A fully configured AttachmentArtifact table that tracks email attachment metadata
    and links to both the source email and the resulting document.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      When users save email attachments, each attachment becomes a separate Document in
      Spaarke. The AttachmentArtifact captures the original attachment metadata (filename,
      content type, size) and links the Document back to its source email.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/sdap-office-integration/spec.md (AttachmentArtifact schema section)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST use sprk_ prefix for all fields</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST link to EmailArtifact parent</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST link to resulting Document</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/plugins.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/DATAVERSE-HOW-TO-CREATE-UPDATE-SCHEMA.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-office-integration/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Create sprk_attachmentartifact table with display name "Attachment Artifact"</step>
    <step order="2">Add sprk_name (Primary Name) - original filename</step>
    <step order="3">Add sprk_originalfilename (Single Line Text, 260 chars)</step>
    <step order="4">Add sprk_contenttype (Single Line Text, 100 chars - MIME type)</step>
    <step order="5">Add sprk_size (Whole Number - bytes)</step>
    <step order="6">Add sprk_contentid (Single Line Text, 256 chars - for inline attachments)</step>
    <step order="7">Add sprk_isinline (Yes/No - true for embedded images)</step>
    <step order="8">Add sprk_emailartifact lookup (N:1 to EmailArtifact)</step>
    <step order="9">Add sprk_document lookup (N:1 to Document - the saved file)</step>
    <step order="10">Configure cascade delete from EmailArtifact (restrict)</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to âœ… completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="pac-cli">Power Platform CLI for solution operations</tool>
    <tool name="power-platform">Power Apps maker portal</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="schema">sprk_attachmentartifact table in Dataverse solution</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-office-integration/notes/schema-attachmentartifact.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Table sprk_attachmentartifact exists in solution</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All specified fields are present with correct types</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">EmailArtifact lookup relationship works</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Document lookup relationship works</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The IsInline flag distinguishes between regular file attachments and inline images
    embedded in HTML email bodies. ContentId is used to match inline attachments with
    their references in the HTML body.
  </notes>

